        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:54AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 454 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sweeny, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Matagorda, Bay City, West Columbia, Sweeny, South Texas Nuclear
Plant, Brazoria, Markham, Sargent, Van Vleck, Wild Peach Village, and
Wadsworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
